<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Eat Neatly</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1003" relname="span">Eating neatly is a sign</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1004" relname="span">that you care about the appearance</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1005" relname="joint">you are presenting at the table</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1006" relname="span">and that you appreciate your food and the effort</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="span">that someone has gone to</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">in putting the food together .</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="contrast">Unless you suffer from a disease</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="10" relname="condition">or you are under the age of 12 years old ,</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1009" relname="span">you should be able to overcome messy eating habits .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1011" relname="joint">Use your silverware properly .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="span">Except for some foods</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1015" relname="same_unit">( sandwiches , pizza , etc ; )</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="same_unit">you have to use your fork and knife .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1018" relname="condition">If you are at a fancy restaurant ,</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="joint">the salad fork is the small fork</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1018" relname="joint">and the larger one is for the main course .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1022" relname="condition">If you are uncertain of these utensils ,</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1022" relname="span">just watch the host ,</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="20" relname="concession">they should know what they are doing .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="23" relname="condition">If you are eating certain foods ,</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1024" relname="span">( steak , etc ; )</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1023" relname="same_unit">you will have to use a knife .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1011" relname="joint">Hold the fork in your left hand and the knife in your right .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1027" relname="preparation">Eat slowly .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">This way you can actually have have a conversation with the person</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="27" relname="elaboration">you are eating with .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1030" relname="span">It also helps you to digest your food properly ,</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1032" relname="condition">which makes you feel more full ,</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1032" relname="joint">so you eat less</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1032" relname="joint">and become fitter ,</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1027" relname="joint">Stay polite throughout the meal .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1035" relname="span">Do n&apos;t hog the conversation ,</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1036" relname="joint">chew with your mouth closed</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1036" relname="joint">and finally , do n&apos;t pick at your food .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1027" relname="joint">Use your napkin .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1027" relname="joint">Always keep it in your lap ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1041" relname="attribution">and if somebody tells you</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="41" relname="condition">that you need to wipe your mouth ,</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1041" relname="span">do n&apos;t get mad about it .</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="43" relname="attribution">Just say ,</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1043" relname="span">&quot; Thank you .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1046" relname="condition">&quot; When you eat with your napkin ,</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">either stuff it down your shirt</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1047" relname="contrast">so you do n&apos;t get it on yourself</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="joint">or put it on your lap</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">and lean more closely to the table</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="circumstance">when you eat .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="51" relname="condition">When you &apos;re full ,</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="span">stop .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1054" relname="span">It &apos;s not impolite</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="52" relname="purpose">to leave food on your plate ,</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1056" relname="condition">and if you are finished</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1056" relname="joint">you could just save it</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1056" relname="joint">and warm the rest up for your supper .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1058" relname="span">Eat as much</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1059" relname="span">as you can</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="58" relname="circumstance">until you feel full ,</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1061" relname="span">but there is an easy way</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="60" relname="purpose">to eat it all .</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1063" relname="joint">Chew it into tiny pieces</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1064" relname="joint">and take smaller amounts</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1065" relname="span">and also after every three mouthfuls stop for a bit</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="64" relname="purpose">to let the food go down .</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1066" relname="joint">If everyone else grabs desert ,</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="joint">and you &apos;re not hungry ,</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1068" relname="joint">do n&apos;t give into &quot; Social Snacking .</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1068" relname="joint">&quot; Instead , keep drinking water in between chats .</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1071" relname="preparation">Turn off your mobile phone .</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1073" relname="condition">However tempting it may be to send a text to everyone about your new pair of shoes ,</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1073" relname="joint">it &apos;s very impolite</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1073" relname="joint">and distracts the entire dinner party .</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1076" relname="span">When eating a food</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="75" relname="elaboration">that drips or has crumbs ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1077" relname="contrast">bring your plate closer to the edge of the table</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1077" relname="contrast">or your mouth closer to the plate .</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="1078" relname="joint">This allows your plate to catch any drips or crumbs</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1078" relname="joint">and avoids a mess .</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1080" relname="span">Keep your posture from slouching</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="81" relname="cause">because it kind of is impolite .</segment>
